        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 2:57PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southeast of Ruidoso Downs, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Whitetail.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
